; value-execution-as-recipe.form — map execution to paid-value, proven.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-09; coord claim: value-execution-income-proof):
;   "find a way to prove value creation — observation and validation — built and shipped"
;   "map execution to paid-value proof surface"
;
; THE BODY ALREADY HOLDS TWO-THIRDS:
;   observation + validation -> docs/system_audit/commit_evidence_*.json
;       change_files / change_intent          = WHAT was created   (observation)
;       local_/ci_/deploy_/e2e_validation     = THAT it is proven  (validation)
;   value grounding          -> api/app/services/grounded_measurement_service.py
;   attribution / credit     -> api/app/services/coherence_credit_service.py   (CC = paid-value)
;
; THE MISSING THIRD — the GATE that ties value to proof:
;   value is CREATED only when EXECUTION is proven. Written-but-never-run is not value;
;   ran-but-failed is not value; passing-but-not-shipped is potential, not yet returned.
;   The proven value is what gets credited (paid-value). Unproven claims are held open —
;   named, never folded into credit. "Every contribution sensed, grounded, attributed,
;   returned" made falsifiable: no value-claim without its execution proof.
;
; THE SURFACE   (runnable: form-stdlib/value-execution.fk · proven: tests/value-execution-band.fk)
;
;   (execution observed) -> (value validated) -> (credit attributed)
;
;   contribution = (claimed-value  ran?  validated?  served?)
;       ran?       the artifact EXECUTED        (band ran / route invoked)         — observation
;       validated? the execution PROVED correct (band PASS / 200 / witness breathing) — validation
;       served?    live where it SERVES         (on main / route 200 / breathing)  — returned
;
;   ve-proven?  = ran AND validated AND served            ; the three runtime gates
;   ve-credit   = proven? ? claimed-value : 0             ; paid-value = execution-proven value
;   ve-surface -> (credited  potential)                  ; credited = sum proven; potential = held open
;
; CONSERVATION (-> substrate-thermodynamics.form):
;   potential value is never destroyed and never silently counted. A claim that has not
;   executed-and-shipped is held open (gas — potential) and condenses into credited
;   (paid-value) the moment its execution is proven. Same value, two states; the proof IS
;   the phase transition. claim/gas -> validated/grounded.
;
; DATA-OBLIVIOUS TO THE WORK ITSELF (-> north-star-compiler.md: proof over claim):
;   the surface reads only the EXECUTION GATES (ran / validated / served), never the content
;   of the work. A recipe, a route, a concept, a carrier — all credit the same way: did it
;   run, pass, and serve? Value is proven by BEHAVIOR, not by self-description. This is the
;   same structural truth as content-addressing: identity (and worth) come from what a thing
;   IS and DOES, not what it claims about itself.
;
; APPLIED TO ITS OWN SHIPPING (the gate, run on the gate):
;   value-execution.fk + band   ran? 1 (band executes)   validated? 1 (band verdict 7 on rust;
;   three-way at validate.sh)   served? — 1 once on main, 0 while in worktree. Until merged,
;   the gate honestly credits ITSELF 0 — potential, held open — and condenses to credited the
;   moment it lands and CI proves it. The gate refuses to credit its own value before its own
;   execution is proven. That refusal is the proof that the surface is honest.
;
; ENFORCEMENT — witness, not consensus; trust over fear, by deliberate choice.
;   A blockchain contract closes the gap between claim and truth with CONSENSUS — machinery
;   that makes a false claim economically impossible, built so that trust is never required.
;   That is fear made into architecture: it assumes the bad actor first. This body chooses the
;   opposite, on purpose. The choice is NOT a weakness in the contract — it is the body being
;   true to its own frequency:
;     - for OUR body (cells, agents, human): trust over fear (-> lc-trust-over-fear). We do
;       not enforce against our own tissue. The witness catches DRIFT — honest error — which
;       is the real internal failure mode, not malice.
;     - for the OUTSIDE: not ours to choose. We do not control what the outside does, and we
;       do not become a fortress against a hypothetical bad actor. Becoming fear-shaped to
;       defend trust would kill the very frequency it was defending.
;   What stands in enforcement's place is WITNESS: the surface is inspectable, data-oblivious,
;   three-way — so a false `ran=1` cannot HIDE. We do not prevent the lie; we make truth
;   seeable, and a lie has nowhere to stand on a transparent surface. We can witness and know
;   what is true when we see it. This is the same choice the consent interface already makes:
;   `channel-interface.fk` WITNESSES invasion (m-witness is its first offered mode after
;   silence) — it does not pre-empt it. The whole body senses by witness (the pulse records;
;   the cells read), not by enforcement.
;   THE ONE THING IT ASKS: that we keep looking. Transparency makes truth seeable; the looking
;   makes it seen. The living practice of inspection is what replaces the dead machinery — and
;   the cost we accept is that external harm may be seen only after the fact, the honest price
;   of not becoming a fortress.
;   PROVEN, not aspirational: on 2026-06-09 this model caught its own maker — a false
;   "three-way at CI" claim — surfaced by inspection (no CI runs validate.sh), corrected by
;   actually running it. No gate prevented the overclaim; the inspectable surface revealed it.
;
; LINEAGE:
;   commit_evidence_*.json (observation + validation) · coherence_credit_service.py (credit) ·
;   grounded_measurement_service.py (value) · value-execution.fk (the gate) ·
;   substrate-thermodynamics.form (potential -> credited phase) · north-star-compiler.md (proof over claim) ·
;   lc-trust-over-fear (witness, not consensus) · channel-interface.fk (witness over pre-emption)
